  <exercises component="web">
    <exercise>
      <p>
	Determine whether the equation <m>2x + 3yx = 3xy + 7y - 4</m> represents a linear function of <m>y</m> in terms of <m>x</m>.
	If so, express the equation in the form <m>y = mx + b</m>.
	Otherwise, explain why the equation does not represent a linear function.
      </p>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <p>
	Determine whether the equation <m>2(x - 2)^2 + y = 3x</m> represents a linear function of <m>y</m> in terms of <m>x</m>.
	If so, express the equation in the form <m>y = mx + b</m>.
	Otherwise, explain why the equation does not represent a linear function.
      </p>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <p>
	Find the <m>x</m>- and <m>y</m>-intercepts of the linear equation <m>5x - 2y = 10</m> and sketch the graph of the equation.
      </p>
      
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <p>
	Match the following equations with their graphs.
	<ol cols="2">
	  <li>
	    <m>y + \frac{6}{4}x - 2 = 0</m>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <m>2y - x + 12 = 2x + 16</m>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <m>3y = 2x - 6</m>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <m>y + x -xy = \frac{1}{3}x - 2 - xy</m>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <m>x + 2y = 1 + x + y</m>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <m>y + x = -1 + x</m>
	  </li>
	</ol>
      </p>
